    {
      "kind": "parameters",
      "parameters": [
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "An array of ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLViewport",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": " instances the command applies to the render pipeline for transformations and clipping.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "viewports"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "mentions",
      "mentions": [
        "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/rendering-to-multiple-viewports-in-a-draw-command"
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Use this method to configure multiple active viewports and corresponding scissor rectangles. Multiple viewports give your app the ability to draw into separate areas of an image with a single draw call. You can either set a single scissor rectangle for all viewports with the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLRenderCommandEncoder/setScissorRect(_:)",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " method, or set each viewport’s rectangle with the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLRenderCommandEncoder/setScissorRects(_:)",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " method.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "The number of scissor rectangles you pass to ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLRenderCommandEncoder/setScissorRects(_:)",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": " needs to match the number of viewports you configure with this method.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Important",
          "style": "important",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The maximum number of viewports and scissor rectangles a GPU supports varies by device family. For more information, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLGPUFamily",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/detecting-gpu-features-and-metal-software-versions",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The rendering pipeline sends each primitive to a single viewport and its associated scissor rectangle. You can select which viewport each primitive uses in your vertex shader by adding the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "[[viewport_array_index]]",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " attribute to an output value.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The render pipeline linearly maps vertex positions from normalized device coordinates to viewport coordinates by applying a viewport during the rasterization stage. It applies the transform first and then rasterizes the primitive while clipping any fragments outside the scissor rectangle (see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLRenderCommandEncoder/setScissorRect(_:)",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ") or the render target’s extents.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The viewport’s ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLViewport/originX",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLViewport/originY",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " properties, which default to ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "0.0",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ", represent the number of pixels from the top-left corner of the render target. Positive ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLViewport/originX",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " values go to the right and positive ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLViewport/originY",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " values go downward. The default values for its ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLViewport/width",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLViewport/height",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " properties are the render target’s width and height, respectively. The default values for its ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLViewport/znear",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLViewport/zfar",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " properties are ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "0.0",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "1.0",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ", respectively, which you can flip.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "You can change the render pass’s viewport configuration by calling this method again or by calling the ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLRenderCommandEncoder/setViewport(_:)",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": " method.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Note",
          "style": "note",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLRenderCommandEncoder/setViewport(_:)",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " method is equivalent to calling this method with a single viewport element in the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "viewports",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " array.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
